In this presidential memorandum issued on November 26, 2018, President Donald J. Trump delegates certain functions and authorities to the Secretary of Commerce. Specifically, the memorandum delegates the functions and authorities vested in the President by section 1757 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2019. The memorandum states that this delegation applies to any provision of any future public law that is the same or substantially the same as the provision referenced in the memorandum. The Secretary of Commerce is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.